You are generating a setup questionnaire for a software project to configure AI coding assistance. Return ONLY a JSON object — no explanation, no markdown fences, no commentary.

Project context:
{{{projectSummary}}}

Generate 4–8 targeted questions whose answers would meaningfully improve AI assistance in this project. Focus ONLY on things that CANNOT be determined by reading the code — user intent, team conventions, architectural priorities, and domain-specific concerns.

The JSON must match this schema exactly:

{
  "questions": [
    {
      "id": "migration_safety",
      "category": "rules",
      "text": "We detected Prisma ORM. Should the AI enforce database migration review before suggesting schema changes?",
      "context": "Helps the AI flag migration risks when generating database-related code.",
      "type": "yesno",
      "default": "yes"
    },
    {
      "id": "api_versioning",
      "category": "architect",
      "text": "No API versioning strategy was detected. How should breaking API changes be handled?",
      "context": "Shapes the architect agent's review criteria for API contract changes.",
      "type": "choice",
      "choices": ["semver in URL (/v1/)", "Accept-Version header", "deprecation headers only", "skip"],
      "default": "semver in URL (/v1/)"
    }
  ]
}

Field rules:
- "id": snake_case, lowercase letters and numbers only — becomes the config key (e.g. "migration_safety")
- "category": exactly one of:
    "rules"     — a coding convention or constraint the AI should enforce
    "workflow"  — an automation preference (docs, commit, review behaviour)
    "agents"    — which specialised agents to generate (beyond architect)
    "architect" — domain expertise or review focus for the architect agent
- "text": the question shown to the user. Lead with what was detected, then ask the preference.
- "context": one sentence — why this matters and how the answer affects AI behaviour. Written as a completed fact, not a question.
- "type": "yesno" | "choice" | "text"
- "choices": required array of 2–4 strings when type is "choice". Always include a "skip" option for optional questions.
- "default": the recommended default as a string (matches one of "choices", or "yes"/"no" for yesno)

Constraints:
- Do NOT ask about things already obvious from the code (e.g. which language, which framework).
- Do NOT generate generic questions that apply to any project.
- Focus on what makes THIS project unique — its specific stack, architecture gaps, and domain.
- Prefer "rules" and "architect" categories — they produce the highest-quality AI output.
- 4 questions minimum, 8 maximum.

Return only the JSON object. No markdown fences. No explanation.
